data.chText: 苏维埃（前苏联的各级代表会议）
data.enText: an elected local, district or national council in the former USSR
the people of the former USSR

means: 苏维埃(前苏联的各级代表会议)

tr: an elected governmental council in a communist country (especially one that is a member of the Union of Soviet Socialist Republics)

value.def: Soviet is used to describe something that belonged or related to the former Soviet Union.
The Soviets were the people of the former Soviet Union.

example.ex: In 1957, the Soviets launched Sputnik 1 into outer space.
example.tran: 1957 年，苏联人将“斯普特尼克1号”人造卫星送入了外层空间。

value.def: A soviet was an elected local, regional, or national council in the former Soviet Union.
value.tran: (苏联的各级)苏维埃，委员会，代表会议
